    <PrimAttribute name="retrospectiveDT" id="9a8faf70-6586-4032-89fc-5b4d727ba11f">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="TimeStamp"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>


This date was added because data like events and other transactions needed to have a date time that is not 'now'. 
Passing the retrospective date through method calls, changing all the references to do this was a big job, that now is unecessary.

Set this date before the TRX. In the Finialize of the TRX it will be nulled.

A similar data is on CMIF_MoveController, this is used for transactions as well, but not all transctions are created during a move.</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="returnCode" id="5b91346d-9f6f-40cb-b672-a9ce4ed8f494">
